WEBVTT

1
00:00:05.635 --> 00:00:07.160
Previously on Prison Break.

2
00:00:07.254 --> 00:00:09.421
Mr. Kim. Sara Tancredi.
I'm on it.

3
00:00:09.456 --> 00:00:11.232
Is pursuing her the
best use of your time?

4
00:00:11.267 --> 00:00:13.009
- It is.
- I'll let the President know.

5
00:00:13.044 --> 00:00:15.830
- I contact the President directly.
- I'll contact her.

6
00:00:21.029 --> 00:00:22.876
No family with
Patoshik? Nothing?

7
00:00:23.119 --> 00:00:25.920
Yeah. Until about four years
ago when he killed them all.

8
00:00:27.470 --> 00:00:30.424
Fernando Sucre-
he was in Las Vegas around 2:00.

9
00:00:30.459 --> 00:00:32.619
Out west.
just like Bagwell and Franklin.

10
00:00:33.154 --> 00:00:34.078
You know D.B. Cooper?

11
00:00:34.113 --> 00:00:36.822
The money's in Utah.
and they're all going to get it.

12
00:00:37.642 --> 00:00:39.298
You're one of them
Fox River boys.

13
00:00:41.000 --> 00:00:47.074
Support us and become VIP member 
to remove all ads from www.OpenSubtitles.org

14
00:00:48.415 --> 00:00:51.719
- Come on. You got the map?
- No. Someone else does.

15
00:00:51.814 --> 00:00:55.737
Before I destroyed it. I committed
it to my photographic memory.

16
00:00:55.845 --> 00:00:59.621
I have the information. you have
the manual requirements necessary

17
00:00:59.718 --> 00:01:02.443
to unearth Westmoreland's
buried booty.

18
00:01:02.588 --> 00:01:04.016
- Get in.
- Okay.

19
00:01:06.424 --> 00:01:08.473
Should be dead ahead.

20
00:01:10.127 --> 00:01:12.605
The bastards built over it.

21
00:01:12.753 --> 00:01:13.312
It's gone.

22
00:02:26.586 --> 00:02:28.518
We have to open
up in 15 minutes.

23
00:02:28.654 --> 00:02:30.356
So. it doesn't matter.
I dare you.

24
00:02:30.490 --> 00:02:32.592
- I said no.
- I dare you. Please?

25
00:03:08.248 --> 00:03:09.930
The ranch is gone. Michael.

26
00:03:11.456 --> 00:03:13.853
Well. the five
million might not be.

27
00:03:13.955 --> 00:03:16.160
And you gonna find it how?

28
00:03:16.255 --> 00:03:18.781
What. you got a divining
rod tattooed on your ass?

29
00:03:18.826 --> 00:03:20.681
I don't want to hear
anything out of your mouth

30
00:03:20.717 --> 00:03:23.061
other than that your
photographic memory spits out

31
00:03:23.088 --> 00:03:24.870
regarding that map.

32
00:03:25.015 --> 00:03:27.062
You watch your
tone with me. boy.

33
00:03:27.157 --> 00:03:31.051
I will watch you get tossed to the side
of the road to fend for yourself. boy.

34
00:03:31.267 --> 00:03:33.942
Because if you can't remember
where that silo was.

35
00:03:34.046 --> 00:03:36.152
you're worthless to us.

36
00:03:36.297 --> 00:03:38.602
- Yo. let me out!
- Shut up!

37
00:03:38.737 --> 00:03:41.043
- The map!
- Uh. uh. okay.

38
00:03:41.135 --> 00:03:43.432
Okay. okay. all right.
all right. all right...

39
00:03:43.617 --> 00:03:46.483
The ranch...
The ranch was in the center of a box-

40
00:03:46.527 --> 00:03:50.150
Sheep Road on one side.
Kokosing Road perpendicular.

41
00:03:50.477 --> 00:03:52.971
In the center of the property
was the ranch house.

42
00:03:53.668 --> 00:03:56.442
And the ranch house was
surrounded by trees.

43
00:04:08.975 --> 00:04:11.941
Every tree here is
a year old at most.

44
00:04:12.596 --> 00:04:14.371
Except those.

45
00:04:16.735 --> 00:04:19.360
Where is the silo?

46
00:04:21.177 --> 00:04:26.402
In... side the trees.
I want to say on the left.

47
00:04:26.868 --> 00:04:29.931
but that may have been a barn.

48
00:04:30.055 --> 00:04:31.901
I remembered the
best I could. gents.

49
00:04:31.977 --> 00:04:35.501
but I didn't know this place would
now be smothered in tract homes.

50
00:04:35.608 --> 00:04:38.840
so. you know. I'm sorry that
I'm not Rainman over here.

51
00:04:43.195 --> 00:04:45.452
- Mahone.
- Lyle Sands.

52
00:04:45.625 --> 00:04:49.223
We've been briefed on all the men at
large. The full force and resources

53
00:04:49.295 --> 00:04:52.441
of the entire Salt Lake City
field office are at your disposal.

54
00:04:52.446 --> 00:04:54.193
Thank you.
Do you have those files my office

55
00:04:54.225 --> 00:04:56.633
- requested on the D.B. Cooper case?
- We're pulling them now.

56
00:04:56.666 --> 00:04:59.213
And this is the D.B.
Cooper case from 30 years ago?

57
00:04:59.307 --> 00:05:02.092
Correct. If I can get those files
immediately. I'd appreciate it.

58
00:05:02.126 --> 00:05:05.982
Hey. sorry. but I have to ask.
Aren't you here for the Fox River Eight?

59
00:05:06.026 --> 00:05:10.691
I am. and they're here in Utah
to get D.B. Cooper's money.

60
00:05:10.786 --> 00:05:12.802
so how about those files. Lyle?

61
00:05:13.687 --> 00:05:14.613
Silo.

62
00:05:14.935 --> 00:05:17.483
Silo. silo. silo. silo.

63
00:05:17.575 --> 00:05:20.303
This is stupid.
We're going to get made out here.

64
00:05:20.486 --> 00:05:23.023
Ah. shut it.
I think I remember.

65
00:05:23.347 --> 00:05:25.793
If I had to bet.
I'd lay it all on the silo

66
00:05:25.935 --> 00:05:28.751
being on the left of the
ranch house inside the trees.

67
00:05:28.877 --> 00:05:33.870
No. It's outside the trees.
Right there.

68
00:05:34.245 --> 00:05:36.210
You see those two trees?

69
00:05:36.315 --> 00:05:38.191
They're shorter than the rest.

70
00:05:38.377 --> 00:05:40.681
They were all planted
at the same time. but

71
00:05:40.775 --> 00:05:42.932
those two didn't get
as much sunlight.

72
00:05:43.077 --> 00:05:46.652
- Something was in their way.
- The silo.

73
00:05:47.065 --> 00:05:50.221
Our money should be right
there under that garage.

74
00:05:50.316 --> 00:05:52.051
You better be right. boy.

75
00:05:52.147 --> 00:05:54.213
This isn't a
high-end subdivision.

76
00:05:54.308 --> 00:05:56.182
They slapped this
place up overnight.

77
00:05:56.326 --> 00:05:58.673
The silo's foundation
might still be there.

78
00:05:58.767 --> 00:06:00.990
To save money.
they probably just laid the concrete

79
00:06:01.027 --> 00:06:03.093
for the garage floor
right on top of it.

80
00:06:03.185 --> 00:06:05.733
We'll dig straight down.
If we hit the foundation. we stay.

81
00:06:05.765 --> 00:06:10.521
- But if not. we go.
- Let's do it.

82
00:06:13.676 --> 00:06:17.672
- Oh. man.
- Uh-uh.

83
00:06:23.188 --> 00:06:27.703
Ain't no problem that a screwdriver
to her temple won't fix.

84
00:06:52.974 --> 00:06:56.704
<i>~ Season 2 - Episode 6 ~
"Subdivision"</i>

85
00:07:06.008 --> 00:07:08.191
People die all the time. boys.

86
00:07:08.317 --> 00:07:10.690
Five million dollars
comes once in a lifetime.

87
00:07:11.347 --> 00:07:13.303
Let me out!

88
00:07:13.396 --> 00:07:15.081
Well. we got to do something.

89
00:07:15.177 --> 00:07:17.660
And it's not going to
involve hurting anyone.

90
00:07:23.038 --> 00:07:27.131
I got an idea. First.
we're going to need some supplies.

91
00:07:44.208 --> 00:07:47.501
110% do not agree with this.

92
00:07:47.646 --> 00:07:50.041
Everybody's got to pitch
in to make this happen.

93
00:07:50.176 --> 00:07:54.081
But back in the big house.
the boy proved he couldn't be trusted.

94
00:07:54.188 --> 00:07:55.831
Which is why we're
doing it here.

95
00:07:55.866 --> 00:07:59.162
If he gets caught in town.
he ain't got a clue where the house is.

96
00:07:59.258 --> 00:08:03.162
Besides. you're the one we
can't turn our backs on.

97
00:08:05.847 --> 00:08:06.873
Oh.

98
00:08:09.048 --> 00:08:11.631
You know.
I could have died in there. man.

99
00:08:13.576 --> 00:08:16.110
Well. guess what?
We need you to do something.

100
00:08:16.215 --> 00:08:20.213
I need you to do something for me.
I want my cut of the money.

101
00:08:20.358 --> 00:08:23.411
Well. we'll talk once you
prove we can trust you.

102
00:08:23.878 --> 00:08:25.203
What do I got to do?

103
00:08:25.248 --> 00:08:26.980
I want you to go back
to that Garden Center

104
00:08:27.018 --> 00:08:32.182
and get everything on this list.
Then gas up the car.

105
00:08:33.845 --> 00:08:36.810
And we'll meet you right
back here in an hour.

106
00:08:38.528 --> 00:08:41.721
- All right.
- And David...

107
00:08:43.855 --> 00:08:46.153
Don't screw this up.

108
00:08:46.345 --> 00:08:49.073
This ain't Fox
River no more. man.

109
00:08:49.488 --> 00:08:52.262
You're looking at
the real deal now.

110
00:08:52.865 --> 00:08:54.880
But I want my cut.

111
00:08:58.076 --> 00:08:59.721
I'll be back in an hour.

112
00:09:05.405 --> 00:09:06.483
Let's go.

113
00:09:08.797 --> 00:09:09.923
Mistake.

114
00:09:10.705 --> 00:09:12.250
Big mistake.

115
00:09:42.266 --> 00:09:43.691
Come on. man.

116
00:10:11.026 --> 00:10:13.613
Am I glad to see you.

117
00:10:14.588 --> 00:10:16.270
Did you walk here?

118
00:10:16.506 --> 00:10:20.563
Well. no... it's...
it's just a long story. man.

119
00:10:20.656 --> 00:10:22.781
Thought you were meeting
up with your family.

120
00:10:22.816 --> 00:10:26.480
I met a...
I met a few roadblocks. You?

121
00:10:26.608 --> 00:10:27.821
Yeah.

122
00:10:28.516 --> 00:10:31.393
Let me guess...
you're going to Tooele.

123
00:10:31.486 --> 00:10:32.413
Yep.

124
00:10:32.835 --> 00:10:36.830
Well. it looks like we're
going in the same direction.

125
00:10:37.347 --> 00:10:41.912
Hopefully we're not too late.
Can I hitch a ride?

126
00:10:43.588 --> 00:10:44.702
Hey...

127
00:10:49.236 --> 00:10:51.281
I'll make it worth your while.

128
00:10:53.698 --> 00:10:55.521
Got some good news. sir.

129
00:10:55.666 --> 00:10:57.631
Got our first tip on Patoshik.

130
00:10:57.736 --> 00:11:01.450
Spotted at a burger joint
in Cedar Grove. Wisconsin.

131
00:11:01.598 --> 00:11:03.481
Just hand it over to
local authorities for now.

132
00:11:03.518 --> 00:11:06.351
The only thing we're working
today is Utah and D.B. Cooper.

133
00:11:06.386 --> 00:11:07.553
Got it.

134
00:11:09.215 --> 00:11:10.050
Lyle.

135
00:11:11.586 --> 00:11:13.333
There's a guy here listed
as having the only

136
00:11:13.365 --> 00:11:16.063
D.B. Cooper bill ever found in
circulation. Harold Jenkins.

137
00:11:16.096 --> 00:11:20.330
Yeah. D.B. bought gas from Jenkins with
a hundred on the day of the hijacking.

138
00:11:20.478 --> 00:11:23.291
We checked the serial
numbers and they matched.

139
00:11:23.388 --> 00:11:27.200
- You worked the case?
- Fresh out of the academy.

140
00:11:27.295 --> 00:11:29.501
And nobody's cracked it yet.

141
00:11:29.595 --> 00:11:32.500
What makes you think that these
escapees know where the money is?

142
00:11:32.537 --> 00:11:35.112
Because they may have been locked
up with the real D.B. Cooper.

143
00:11:35.147 --> 00:11:37.510
This Jenkins from the gas station.
he still alive?

144
00:11:37.547 --> 00:11:40.080
Should be.
He was only 18 at the time.

145
00:11:40.172 --> 00:11:42.159
Let's go say hi to him.

146
00:12:16.257 --> 00:12:19.363
We're sorry.
Your call cannot be completed as dialed.

147
00:12:19.456 --> 00:12:21.853
Please check the
number and dial again.

148
00:12:37.555 --> 00:12:40.903
I'm assuming you're here because
you have updates on Sara Tancredi?

149
00:12:40.987 --> 00:12:45.513
Yes. um. Scofield sent her
a message through the mail.

150
00:12:45.606 --> 00:12:48.430
that phone number that
was disconnected.

151
00:12:50.378 --> 00:12:52.773
You know. to be honest. uh.

152
00:12:53.035 --> 00:12:55.420
I was expecting to
brief the President.

153
00:12:57.525 --> 00:13:00.213
Yeah. about that. uh.

154
00:13:00.347 --> 00:13:03.030
right now. as you can imagine.

155
00:13:03.175 --> 00:13:05.750
- Caroline's quite busy.
- She's always been busy.

156
00:13:05.896 --> 00:13:08.493
I've been working side-by-side
with her for 15 years.

157
00:13:08.528 --> 00:13:11.251
Paul. she's the President
of the United States now.

158
00:13:11.445 --> 00:13:14.310
Yes. Bill.
and I helped put her there.

159
00:13:14.438 --> 00:13:17.113
Well. if you'd like for
her to remain in office.

160
00:13:17.298 --> 00:13:20.350
you'll take my advice and just
stay on the sidelines for now.

161
00:13:21.937 --> 00:13:26.033
She needs to be completely insulated
from anything regarding Lincoln Burrows.

162
00:13:29.227 --> 00:13:31.103
I want to talk to her.

163
00:13:33.418 --> 00:13:36.461
You report to me now.
and only me.

164
00:13:36.508 --> 00:13:39.160
You're not to try and contact
Caroline again without my approval.

165
00:13:39.198 --> 00:13:43.253
and you don't show
up here unannounced.

166
00:13:45.056 --> 00:13:48.252
Finish the job you were given;
get Burrows.

167
00:13:49.188 --> 00:13:52.851
If you're telling me the road to
him leads through Sara Tancredi.

168
00:13:53.137 --> 00:13:55.202
by all means. pursue it.

169
00:13:55.336 --> 00:13:58.583
And once that's been accomplished
and this whole thing goes away.

170
00:13:59.048 --> 00:14:02.670
we'll go about transitioning
you back into Caroline's life.

171
00:14:05.678 --> 00:14:07.880
Now do you have
anything else on Sara?

172
00:14:07.978 --> 00:14:10.372
The President has
unwavering faith in you.

173
00:14:10.617 --> 00:14:12.360
Wants to make sure
you go through the

174
00:14:12.398 --> 00:14:14.841
Senate approval process
with your eyes wide open.

175
00:14:14.938 --> 00:14:16.112
So what are we up against?

176
00:14:16.145 --> 00:14:19.900
Key allies in the House and Senate are
Meyerhoff. Barnwell and Summerville.

177
00:14:20.005 --> 00:14:21.680
We're counting on them
to sway the middle.

178
00:14:21.718 --> 00:14:22.962
But who's the opposition?

179
00:14:23.117 --> 00:14:26.993
Senators Blake and Killoren have openly
vocalized their opposition to you as VP.

180
00:14:27.026 --> 00:14:28.713
Any indications to why?

181
00:14:29.085 --> 00:14:32.800
Political payback for the President's
vote on the energy bill last month.

182
00:14:32.946 --> 00:14:35.860
Took them by surprise and
they don't like surprises.

183
00:14:40.056 --> 00:14:44.290
- Lance. this is. uh. my father Frank.
- Pleasure to meet you. sir.

184
00:14:44.855 --> 00:14:46.452
It's nothing to
lose sleep over.

185
00:14:46.498 --> 00:14:48.741
Frankly. the biggest
issue we have to address

186
00:14:49.167 --> 00:14:51.423
are the charges
facing your daughter.

187
00:14:51.836 --> 00:14:53.431
Governor. are you with me?

188
00:14:54.128 --> 00:14:56.431
Absolutely.

189
00:15:10.497 --> 00:15:13.732
No. just chill. dawg. Listen.

190
00:15:13.866 --> 00:15:16.312
once we roll out.
we bounce out of town.

191
00:15:16.457 --> 00:15:19.231
we'll drop a dime and
they will find you.

192
00:15:19.328 --> 00:15:21.393
Just be quiet. Just chill. man.

193
00:15:37.917 --> 00:15:38.992
Woody?

194
00:15:41.487 --> 00:15:44.313
Where you at? Woody?

195
00:16:00.977 --> 00:16:02.992
I need Sheriff Williams.

196
00:16:03.736 --> 00:16:05.513
Yeah. I'll hold.

197
00:16:12.546 --> 00:16:13.762
Woody?

198
00:16:29.088 --> 00:16:30.830
When'd you learn
about electricity?

199
00:16:30.868 --> 00:16:33.513
I used to steal copper wiring
from transformer boxes.

200
00:16:33.595 --> 00:16:36.133
Sell 'em on the docks.
make a few bucks.

201
00:16:36.365 --> 00:16:38.671
When you were at school.
of course.

202
00:16:49.477 --> 00:16:51.491
I was just looking. Pretty.

203
00:16:51.617 --> 00:16:53.210
What's that old chestnut?

204
00:16:53.395 --> 00:16:55.673
"I can look at the menu.
Doesn't mean I'm gonna eat. "

205
00:16:55.705 --> 00:16:58.900
We get in. we get the money. we get out.
That's it.

206
00:16:59.086 --> 00:17:00.252
No. absolutely.

207
00:17:11.458 --> 00:17:12.673
We're good.

208
00:17:15.768 --> 00:17:18.070
Now it's just up to the kid.

209
00:17:23.395 --> 00:17:24.651
Did you get everything?

210
00:17:24.846 --> 00:17:26.432
Yeah. Yeah. I got it.

211
00:17:47.306 --> 00:17:48.041
What?

212
00:17:48.277 --> 00:17:50.481
Nothing. It's cool.
I handled it.

213
00:17:50.628 --> 00:17:51.841
- Whoa!
- What?!

214
00:17:51.985 --> 00:17:52.631
Whoa.

215
00:17:53.237 --> 00:17:55.862
Okay. Check it.

216
00:17:56.108 --> 00:17:57.830
This fool came in the shop.

217
00:17:57.925 --> 00:17:59.910
He was acting all shady.
He got a bad vibe.

218
00:17:59.945 --> 00:18:03.583
so he picked up his celly phone. he
started to make a call. so I popped him.

219
00:18:03.615 --> 00:18:04.973
You did what?!

220
00:18:05.146 --> 00:18:07.972
I hit him with a shovel. man!
I didn't know what else to do!

221
00:18:08.008 --> 00:18:09.800
So I just. I tied him up and

222
00:18:09.837 --> 00:18:12.103
in put him in the back room
with that other country hick.

223
00:18:12.138 --> 00:18:15.052
- Here we go. Here we go.
- I came through. you gimp!

224
00:18:15.425 --> 00:18:18.721
- Who was he calling?
- The sheriff.

225
00:18:18.906 --> 00:18:22.100
Man. man. I don't know. dude.
It just. it set off...

226
00:18:22.145 --> 00:18:24.491
- Did the call go through?!
- Maybe. man...

227
00:18:24.538 --> 00:18:26.583
What do you mean. maybe?
Did the call go through?!

228
00:18:26.615 --> 00:18:34.963
Yes. No. I don't know! I don't know.
man. Yo. but I got the gear.

229
00:18:35.518 --> 00:18:37.391
We got to move on this now.

230
00:18:38.728 --> 00:18:39.652
Yes?

231
00:18:40.907 --> 00:18:44.103
Sorry to bother you. ma'am.
Is your electricity out?

232
00:18:45.028 --> 00:18:47.282
Excuse me.
I'm looking for a Harold Jenkins.

233
00:18:47.427 --> 00:18:51.942
- Right here.
- Alexander Mahone. FBI.

234
00:18:52.086 --> 00:18:54.310
I'm staying 50 feet away
from her at all times.

235
00:18:54.347 --> 00:18:56.450
What the hell else
does she want?

236
00:18:56.598 --> 00:18:58.333
I'm not here about that.

237
00:18:59.396 --> 00:19:01.983
- What are you here for?
- D.B. Cooper.

238
00:19:02.307 --> 00:19:06.402
People still want to know
about that guy? Unbelievable.

239
00:19:06.576 --> 00:19:09.532
You worked the gas station in
American Fork where he filled up.

240
00:19:09.567 --> 00:19:14.130
Yeah. Normal-looking guy.
Barely said a word.

241
00:19:14.275 --> 00:19:17.770
There were some discrepancies in the
statement you filed 30 years ago.

242
00:19:17.896 --> 00:19:21.520
In the report. it's noted that you
said he filled up at 7:00 a. m..

243
00:19:21.755 --> 00:19:25.502
but on another occasion.
you said it was 7:00 p. m.

244
00:19:25.596 --> 00:19:28.282
- Which was it?
- Both.

245
00:19:29.287 --> 00:19:32.342
- He gassed up twice?
- Yeah.

246
00:19:32.805 --> 00:19:38.220
- Full tanks both times?
- Yeah. Why?

247
00:19:39.015 --> 00:19:41.120
A systems what?

248
00:19:41.265 --> 00:19:43.050
It's a systems
diagnostics test.

249
00:19:43.515 --> 00:19:47.651
Footage from our gopher cam picked up
exactly where your line was corrupted.

250
00:19:47.755 --> 00:19:52.372
- And who corrupted it. you guys?
- Maybe.

251
00:19:52.465 --> 00:19:55.530
All I know is my supervisor called
and said he wants me and my crew

252
00:19:55.565 --> 00:20:00.043
to get over here and fix that
problem double-quick. double-time.

253
00:20:00.138 --> 00:20:04.801
So... you're not with
the electric company?

254
00:20:04.927 --> 00:20:08.003
No. ma'am.
Now feel free to call your company.

255
00:20:08.038 --> 00:20:10.533
but I should tell you.
all they'll do is send over some tech.

256
00:20:10.565 --> 00:20:12.583
maybe tomorrow if you're lucky.

257
00:20:12.755 --> 00:20:15.620
And he'll spend a whole day
trying to find the problem

258
00:20:15.746 --> 00:20:17.862
and another day
trying to fix it.

259
00:20:18.606 --> 00:20:24.581
But we're here right now and we're
ready to turn your juice back on.

260
00:20:24.958 --> 00:20:28.161
- My juice?
- That's right.

261
00:20:30.176 --> 00:20:32.382
And. uh...

262
00:20:32.948 --> 00:20:36.610
and that's your... crew?

263
00:20:39.576 --> 00:20:41.070
Yes. ma'am.

264
00:20:41.865 --> 00:20:45.393
Yeah. D.B.
Cooper was driving a 1965 Chevy Nova.

265
00:20:45.545 --> 00:20:48.501
There's no record on file
that Cooper even had a car.

266
00:20:48.637 --> 00:20:51.611
But Charles Westmoreland did. and
the car registered to him at the time

267
00:20:51.645 --> 00:20:55.223
was a 1965 Chevy Nova with
a 16-gallon gas tank.

268
00:20:55.367 --> 00:20:59.183
Back then. a Chevy that size probably
got what. eight miles to the gallon?

269
00:20:59.276 --> 00:21:01.812
Now. D.B.
stopped at the station in American Fork.

270
00:21:01.956 --> 00:21:03.642
gassed up once early that day

271
00:21:03.785 --> 00:21:06.661
and then came back later that
same night and gassed up again.

272
00:21:06.695 --> 00:21:10.103
Now. why would a guy headed to Mexico.
which is a straight shot south.

273
00:21:10.135 --> 00:21:13.051
drive off the main road
for an all-day detour?

274
00:21:13.187 --> 00:21:13.680
The money.

275
00:21:13.796 --> 00:21:18.641
Exactly. Cooper/Westmoreland jumped
out of a plane with $5 million.

276
00:21:19.945 --> 00:21:22.951
But Westmoreland didn't have the
money on him when he was arrested.

277
00:21:22.985 --> 00:21:26.083
He ditched it before he got caught.
Give me that Magic Marker.

278
00:21:26.138 --> 00:21:30.322
From American Fork. he couldn't have gone
further than 64 miles in any direction.

279
00:21:30.416 --> 00:21:32.453
I want everything you've
got in that perimeter.

280
00:21:32.486 --> 00:21:34.232
Those cons are in one
of these towns. and

281
00:21:34.266 --> 00:21:38.062
if there's so much as a cat missing in
one of them. I want to know about it.

282
00:21:41.357 --> 00:21:44.043
The defective cable runs
right beneath your garage.

283
00:21:44.226 --> 00:21:47.563
We're gonna have to dig up
the floor to get to it.

284
00:21:49.235 --> 00:21:51.250
Well. who's gonna pay for this

285
00:21:51.347 --> 00:21:53.701
and what about the
cleanup and the repair?

286
00:21:53.795 --> 00:21:55.762
Well. the company
will cover all costs.

287
00:21:56.597 --> 00:21:58.422
We'll just dig a small trench.

288
00:21:58.525 --> 00:22:00.551
once we're finished.
we'll re-lay the cement.

289
00:22:00.587 --> 00:22:02.232
It'll look as good as new.

290
00:22:02.327 --> 00:22:04.011
How long is it going to take?

291
00:22:04.478 --> 00:22:07.342
One way or another.
we'll be out of here today.

292
00:22:07.766 --> 00:22:09.612
We really need to
get started. ma'am.

293
00:22:11.445 --> 00:22:14.381
We wouldn't want a pretty
little thing like yourself

294
00:22:14.527 --> 00:22:17.211
sitting in the dark tonight.
now do we?

295
00:22:17.347 --> 00:22:21.301
Now that depends on
who I'm sitting with.

296
00:22:21.447 --> 00:22:22.522
Touche.

297
00:22:26.456 --> 00:22:31.402
Fine. that's okay. y'all go ahead
and do whatever y'all need to do.

298
00:22:31.498 --> 00:22:33.652
Jeanette. the noise
might be substantial.

299
00:22:34.028 --> 00:22:36.561
You might want take in that
tennis game after all.

300
00:22:36.758 --> 00:22:39.903
Oh. no it's...
it's too hot for that now.

301
00:22:40.045 --> 00:22:41.843
Plus. I'm gonna keep
an eye on y'all

302
00:22:41.996 --> 00:22:44.820
and make sure you
don't steal anything.

303
00:22:44.956 --> 00:22:45.892
Ma'am.

304
00:22:50.847 --> 00:22:53.243
- How are you?
- Good.

305
00:22:55.555 --> 00:22:57.001
All right. where's Tweener?

306
00:22:57.195 --> 00:22:59.222
He's next door plugging
in the extension cord.

307
00:22:59.255 --> 00:23:01.302
We're going to have
to cut up the cement.

308
00:23:01.505 --> 00:23:04.232
Yo. we gots company.

309
00:23:09.697 --> 00:23:11.991
What's up. snowflake?

310
00:23:15.356 --> 00:23:17.750
As always.
your timing is flawless.

311
00:23:19.425 --> 00:23:20.542
I don't follow.

312
00:23:20.635 --> 00:23:22.103
Well. let me try to
explain it to you.

313
00:23:22.135 --> 00:23:23.740
We're trying to
run something here

314
00:23:23.777 --> 00:23:26.130
and we can't have people
walking in off the street.

315
00:23:26.165 --> 00:23:29.652
Oh. oh. okay.
so you want us to leave

316
00:23:29.835 --> 00:23:31.952
and then you can just
mail us the check?

317
00:23:33.946 --> 00:23:35.723
Sucre. I know you trust me.

318
00:23:36.405 --> 00:23:38.752
And you know I'll cut
you in on that money.

319
00:23:38.897 --> 00:23:42.611
But the two of you being here
right now jeopardizes everything.

320
00:23:43.636 --> 00:23:47.733
I'm not going nowhere.
I want my share of the money.

321
00:23:47.865 --> 00:23:51.070
Wait a minute. Hold on. man.
Ain't we did this dance before?

322
00:23:51.165 --> 00:23:53.942
You know. I say I want in.
you say no.

323
00:23:54.495 --> 00:23:58.730
Then I threaten to tell somebody
about what's going on here.

324
00:23:58.878 --> 00:24:02.780
Then you decide to play nice and
then we're one big. happy family.

325
00:24:03.575 --> 00:24:07.293
Why don't we just stop wasting time.
all right?

326
00:24:12.156 --> 00:24:13.221
Thank you.

327
00:24:20.765 --> 00:24:23.351
Damn. man. you still alive?

328
00:24:24.837 --> 00:24:28.741
- And kickin'. home boy.
- How'd you find us?

329
00:24:28.885 --> 00:24:32.220
Man. if I can do rapid deployment
of satellite communications

330
00:24:32.318 --> 00:24:34.711
for Uncle Sam all
over the world...

331
00:24:35.276 --> 00:24:38.191
How are you guys doing?

332
00:24:38.517 --> 00:24:41.103
Who are you? Who are they?

333
00:24:41.286 --> 00:24:43.681
I. uh.
I had to call my supervisor.

334
00:24:43.877 --> 00:24:46.473
He sent them right over.
This job is a top priority.

335
00:24:46.506 --> 00:24:50.290
We want to get this done as quickly
and efficiently as possible.

336
00:25:02.556 --> 00:25:04.292
Well. Jeanette. like I said.

337
00:25:04.437 --> 00:25:07.230
there's a lot of work to do.
and it's going to be noisy.

338
00:25:07.255 --> 00:25:11.871
- Oh. drinks. I forgot to ask.
- We're good. Thanks.

339
00:25:21.957 --> 00:25:24.121
Yo. man. this is not good.

340
00:25:24.218 --> 00:25:27.700
We got her up in our grill
checking in on us all the time.

341
00:25:27.938 --> 00:25:30.090
The boy is right.

342
00:25:30.348 --> 00:25:35.861
And since I can't dig.
I'll volunteer to keep her occupied.

343
00:25:36.376 --> 00:25:38.201
You don't touch her.

344
00:25:38.345 --> 00:25:42.581
Who are you. Sister Mary Francis?
I know how to play nice.

345
00:25:42.766 --> 00:25:44.742
I'll be watching.

346
00:26:36.886 --> 00:26:39.230
Billy? Is that you?

347
00:26:47.887 --> 00:26:50.282
Billy? Is that you?

348
00:26:54.707 --> 00:26:55.643
Yep.

349
00:26:57.817 --> 00:26:58.741
Oh.

350
00:27:02.905 --> 00:27:04.553
Thank you kindly.

351
00:27:07.057 --> 00:27:11.383
Well now.
how did you get out of working?

352
00:27:12.128 --> 00:27:13.671
Union rules.

353
00:27:13.998 --> 00:27:17.152
Uh. one crew member
always has to supervise.

354
00:27:17.798 --> 00:27:21.332
I'll check on them in a bit.

355
00:27:23.467 --> 00:27:25.191
- Lemonade?
- Mm.

356
00:27:25.935 --> 00:27:27.673
Hmm...

357
00:27:32.955 --> 00:27:34.151
More ice.

358
00:27:38.738 --> 00:27:46.230
Yeah. And I like mine
with a little... Oops.

359
00:27:46.696 --> 00:27:52.072
But since you're on the clock.
I guess you can't...

360
00:27:52.348 --> 00:27:54.030
join me?

361
00:27:55.837 --> 00:27:57.623
Just two fingers.

362
00:28:21.545 --> 00:28:22.902
Been a while.

363
00:28:23.317 --> 00:28:24.060
Yeah?

364
00:28:29.746 --> 00:28:32.700
Whiskey always makes me feel...

365
00:28:33.167 --> 00:28:35.142
irascible.

366
00:28:35.927 --> 00:28:38.651
I don't know what that means.

367
00:28:39.348 --> 00:28:42.882
But I do like the sound of it.

368
00:28:48.248 --> 00:28:51.072
Are you wearing Angel perfume?

369
00:28:52.466 --> 00:28:54.431
I am.

370
00:28:58.136 --> 00:29:01.053
Oh. hmm...

371
00:29:01.656 --> 00:29:05.421
That reminds you of an ex.
I take it.

372
00:29:05.566 --> 00:29:06.301
Yeah.

373
00:29:08.625 --> 00:29:12.101
Now. was that good memories...

374
00:29:12.287 --> 00:29:15.351
or bad memories?

375
00:29:17.108 --> 00:29:18.681
Both.

376
00:29:28.678 --> 00:29:32.353
- Did you talk to Maricruz?
- I don't want to talk about it.

377
00:29:32.955 --> 00:29:35.730
I got to get some
water or something.

378
00:29:36.197 --> 00:29:38.572
Use the hose on the
other side of the house.

379
00:29:41.626 --> 00:29:42.932
Sucre...

380
00:29:43.267 --> 00:29:44.552
down the road.

381
00:29:44.968 --> 00:29:49.212
if you're in
trouble. europeangoldfinch. net.

382
00:29:51.387 --> 00:29:53.730
It's what we can all
use to communicate.

383
00:29:53.875 --> 00:29:55.940
Post a note on
the message board.

384
00:29:57.828 --> 00:30:01.780
- What's it called?
- Europeangoldfinch. net.

385
00:30:02.107 --> 00:30:03.743
That's a bird. right?

386
00:30:10.366 --> 00:30:12.103
I got something.

387
00:30:18.675 --> 00:30:20.553
It's the silo's foundation.

388
00:30:20.697 --> 00:30:21.861
Hells. yeah.

389
00:30:22.608 --> 00:30:24.243
Thank you. Charles.

390
00:30:24.665 --> 00:30:28.882
We just need to find the
edge and dig underneath it.

391
00:30:29.206 --> 00:30:31.062
We'll get the money...

392
00:30:31.437 --> 00:30:34.020
hit the back roads.

393
00:30:34.258 --> 00:30:37.412
- Uh. well...
- What's wrong?

394
00:30:39.535 --> 00:30:43.772
We gots to stop in Tooele
first and gas up the ride.

395
00:30:43.895 --> 00:30:45.411
I thought you already did that.

396
00:30:45.448 --> 00:30:48.842
Man. when the garden center thing
happened I just forgot. all right?

397
00:30:49.827 --> 00:30:52.643
I want you to go
back into town-

398
00:30:52.788 --> 00:30:54.710
I want you to gas up that car.

399
00:30:54.856 --> 00:30:57.830
Because I'm not driving around with
millions of dollars in the trunk.

400
00:30:57.865 --> 00:30:58.982
do you understand?

401
00:30:59.078 --> 00:31:01.142
Man. why do I gots to do it...?

402
00:31:01.285 --> 00:31:02.261
Okay.

403
00:31:03.605 --> 00:31:04.721
Okay.

404
00:31:14.815 --> 00:31:17.490
Better check in on our friend.

405
00:31:22.908 --> 00:31:24.453
Miss Tinsel Toes.

406
00:31:34.157 --> 00:31:35.183
Billy?

407
00:31:38.006 --> 00:31:39.031
Billy?

408
00:31:40.507 --> 00:31:41.543
Yeah.

409
00:31:42.005 --> 00:31:43.783
I made you a sandwich.

410
00:31:44.247 --> 00:31:47.680
Peanut butter and jelly
with the crusts cut off.

411
00:31:48.105 --> 00:31:49.693
Just like you like.

412
00:31:54.645 --> 00:31:56.952
I'm so glad you came back.

413
00:31:58.017 --> 00:32:00.773
I don't want to say
I told you so. but

414
00:32:00.865 --> 00:32:03.923
that was just not
the girl for you.

415
00:32:09.335 --> 00:32:11.262
Where is that?

416
00:32:11.725 --> 00:32:13.961
Where's what. sweetheart?

417
00:32:14.476 --> 00:32:16.543
That painting.

418
00:32:17.126 --> 00:32:18.910
Oh. it's Holland.

419
00:32:19.048 --> 00:32:21.631
Where I grew up. You know that.

420
00:32:23.077 --> 00:32:24.803
It's beautiful.

421
00:32:25.137 --> 00:32:27.291
Oh. there's no place better.

422
00:32:27.436 --> 00:32:34.222
It's so peaceful. so...
so protected from this crazy world.

423
00:32:47.716 --> 00:32:52.800
Hello. Operator?
There's an intruder in my house...

424
00:32:57.527 --> 00:33:00.910
Hello. ma'am? Ma'am?
Are you there?

425
00:33:01.607 --> 00:33:02.922
Is anyone there?

426
00:33:06.897 --> 00:33:09.393
Heard you had some
activity in Tooele today.

427
00:33:09.577 --> 00:33:12.350
A bit. Don't see how it
warrants a visit from the FBI.

428
00:33:12.536 --> 00:33:14.610
A stolen car was dumped
just outside of town.

429
00:33:14.646 --> 00:33:17.960
belonging to a woman who went to school
in St. Louis. am I getting that right?

430
00:33:17.998 --> 00:33:18.731
Yes. sir.

431
00:33:19.158 --> 00:33:22.730
And then here. the owner's
girlfriend reports him missing.

432
00:33:22.878 --> 00:33:25.473
and then his buddy comes by
to check it out and he...

433
00:33:25.508 --> 00:33:26.911
goes missing. too.

434
00:33:27.047 --> 00:33:29.882
Yeah. but Woody and Chet have
been known to drop everything

435
00:33:29.916 --> 00:33:32.662
and go boar hunting when the
opportunity presents itself.

436
00:33:32.696 --> 00:33:34.540
and they don't tell
their old ladies.

437
00:33:37.895 --> 00:33:41.593
Mr. Mahone. I'll bet you my lunch money
there's nothing amiss around here.

438
00:33:44.257 --> 00:33:47.263
But Woody's dad'll be showing
up soon with the keys and...

439
00:33:47.355 --> 00:33:48.653
you can look for yourself.

440
00:33:48.766 --> 00:33:50.361
Whoa. whoa.
What are you doing?!

441
00:33:56.736 --> 00:33:58.143
Mr. Mahone.

442
00:33:58.655 --> 00:33:59.682
Shh.

443
00:34:12.868 --> 00:34:14.082
They're here.

444
00:34:14.225 --> 00:34:16.852
Those escaped convicts.
They're here in town.

445
00:34:44.825 --> 00:34:46.130
Who's there?

446
00:34:46.965 --> 00:34:50.023
It's the police. ma'am.
You okay?

447
00:34:50.638 --> 00:34:51.992
Yes.

448
00:34:53.885 --> 00:34:55.382
Can you tell me what happened?

449
00:34:55.437 --> 00:34:56.880
There was this strange man.

450
00:34:57.577 --> 00:35:01.633
I made him a peanut
butter sandwich.

451
00:35:01.767 --> 00:35:04.071
I thought he was Billy.

452
00:35:07.865 --> 00:35:11.773
And once the kids went to sleep.
we'd take a bath.

453
00:35:13.345 --> 00:35:16.361
A long... bath.

454
00:35:16.507 --> 00:35:20.970
And afterwards.
I'd just sit there and watch her...

455
00:35:21.166 --> 00:35:23.163
do her routine. see.

456
00:35:23.306 --> 00:35:26.122
Rub her lotion on.
comb her hair.

457
00:35:26.268 --> 00:35:29.943
Dress up in her
nighttime fineries.

458
00:35:30.086 --> 00:35:32.333
Oh. you're killing me.

459
00:35:34.466 --> 00:35:39.222
She had this spot on
her neck right... here.

460
00:35:41.255 --> 00:35:43.981
Gave her goosebumps every time.

461
00:35:49.007 --> 00:35:51.641
And that perfume...

462
00:35:57.058 --> 00:35:58.362
My ex.

463
00:35:59.617 --> 00:36:01.681
He was an accountant.

464
00:36:02.565 --> 00:36:05.191
He was really buttoned up.

465
00:36:05.475 --> 00:36:09.711
He was ram. damn.
thank you. Sam.

466
00:36:10.916 --> 00:36:12.980
Well. shame on him.

467
00:36:15.855 --> 00:36:21.032
Why did it end with that
lady you were talking about?

468
00:36:26.686 --> 00:36:29.832
Just went out separate ways.

469
00:36:35.845 --> 00:36:37.771
Do you know...

470
00:36:37.916 --> 00:36:41.400
what I think the best cure
is for a broken heart?

471
00:36:42.746 --> 00:36:44.432
Do tell.

472
00:36:45.815 --> 00:36:48.363
Get back on the bike.

473
00:36:49.606 --> 00:36:51.810
Whatever bike it is.

474
00:36:55.305 --> 00:36:57.981
Amen to that.

475
00:36:58.987 --> 00:37:00.913
Speaking of.

476
00:37:02.417 --> 00:37:05.621
Could you do something for me?

477
00:37:07.237 --> 00:37:09.493
I'm certain of it.

478
00:37:12.085 --> 00:37:13.490
Come here.

479
00:37:15.487 --> 00:37:18.631
Only you have to
be very discreet.

480
00:37:20.306 --> 00:37:23.501
They don't come any discreter.

481
00:37:23.685 --> 00:37:29.440
You know that. that big guy the
strong guy that. that doesn't...

482
00:37:29.626 --> 00:37:32.213
speak much?

483
00:37:32.396 --> 00:37:34.652
Would you go in
there and ask him

484
00:37:34.797 --> 00:37:41.250
if he would like to have a drink with
me after he punches out? Please.

485
00:37:43.285 --> 00:37:46.160
You've just been playing me
this whole time. haven't you?

486
00:37:46.345 --> 00:37:50.490
Come on. Don't be like that.

487
00:37:51.097 --> 00:37:55.002
Would you just go in and
ask your friend? Please?

488
00:38:16.606 --> 00:38:17.541
Hey. Dad.

489
00:38:17.686 --> 00:38:19.531
Sarah. I've been
trying to reach you.

490
